    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1161" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀπειλέω</span></b> , fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">-ήσω</span>, ipf. du. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀπειλήτην</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">threaten, menace;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινί</span>, regularly foll. by fut. inf.;
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γέρας αὐτὸς ἀφαιρήσεσθαι ἀπειλεῖς</span>,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 1.161</span></i>; freq. w. cognate acc.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀπειλά̄ς,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 16.201</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            μῦθον</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.388</span></i>; less
          specifically, ‘boast,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 8.150</span></i>
          (foll. by <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἶναι</span>), <i><span class="en">Od. 8.383</span></i>; ‘vow,’ ‘promise,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 23.863</span></i>, 872.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
